The paper deals with natural language processing and reasoning, which are core topics in the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of state-of-the-art language models and information retrieval techniques also suggests a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper's focus on improving accuracy through re-ranking and weighted scoring techniques suggests a connection to Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
